description:
**MEMORY CONSTRAINT**

Implement LRU eviction for hot index to prevent DO memory exhaustion.

## Target File
`packages/do-core/src/hot-index-lru.ts`

## Implementation
```typescript
export class LRUHotIndex<T> {
  private readonly maxSize: number
  private readonly cache = new Map<string, { value: T; accessedAt: number }>()

  constructor(options: { maxSize: number; onEvict?: (entries: T[]) => Promise<void> }) {
    this.maxSize = options.maxSize
  }

  get(key: string): T | undefined {
    const entry = this.cache.get(key)
    if (entry) entry.accessedAt = Date.now()
    return entry?.value
  }

  set(key: string, value: T): void {
    if (this.cache.size >= this.maxSize) {
      this.evictLRU()
    }
    this.cache.set(key, { value, accessedAt: Date.now() })
  }
}
```

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] All RED tests pass
- [ ] O(1) get/set operations
- [ ] Configurable onEvict callback for warm migration

