Implement sysparm_fields parameter to filter returned fields.

## Implementation Requirements
1. Parse comma-separated sysparm_fields parameter
2. Build SELECT clause with only requested fields
3. Handle empty/missing parameter (return all fields)
4. Support dot-walking for reference field attributes

## Dot-Walking Implementation
```typescript
function buildSelectClause(tableName: string, fields: string[]): string {
  const columns = fields.map(field => {
    if (field.includes('.')) {
      // Dot-walk: caller_id.email -> JOIN sys_user ON ... SELECT email AS "caller_id.email"
      const [refField, attr] = field.split('.')
      return buildJoinForDotWalk(tableName, refField, attr)
    }
    return field
  })
  return columns.join(', ')
}
```

## SQL Generation Example
```sql
-- Request: sysparm_fields=number,caller_id.name
SELECT 
  incident.number,
  sys_user.name AS "caller_id.name"
FROM incident
LEFT JOIN sys_user ON incident.caller_id = sys_user.sys_id
```

