## Implementation
Reuse condition evaluator from views, adding trigger-specific conditions.

```typescript
class TriggerConditionEvaluator extends ConditionEvaluator {
  evaluate(
    ticket: Ticket,
    conditions: Conditions,
    context: TriggerContext
  ): boolean {
    // Check update_type first
    if (!this.matchesUpdateType(context)) return false

    // Then evaluate all/any conditions
    return super.evaluate(ticket, conditions, context)
  }

  private matchesUpdateType(context: TriggerContext): boolean {
    const updateTypeCondition = this.findUpdateTypeCondition()
    if (!updateTypeCondition) return true  // No restriction

    return context.isCreate 
      ? updateTypeCondition.value === 'Create'
      : updateTypeCondition.value === 'Change'
  }
}

interface TriggerContext extends EvalContext {
  isCreate: boolean
  viaChannel: string
  comment?: string
}
```

## Trigger-Specific Operators
- subject_includes_word: Check if subject contains word
- comment_includes_word: Check if latest comment contains word
- current_via_id: Match request channel (web=0, email=4, api=8)

