## Problem
Schema initialization runs on every request instead of using blockConcurrencyWhile in constructor.

## Test Requirements
```typescript
describe('Schema Initialization', () => {
  it('should use blockConcurrencyWhile', () => {
    const mockState = {
      blockConcurrencyWhile: jest.fn()
    };
    new DO(mockState, env);
    expect(mockState.blockConcurrencyWhile).toHaveBeenCalled();
  });

  it('should only initialize once', async () => {
    const initSpy = jest.spyOn(SchemaMigrations, 'initialize');
    const do = new DO(state, env);
    await do.fetch(request1);
    await do.fetch(request2);
    expect(initSpy).toHaveBeenCalledTimes(1);
  });
});
```

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] Test verifies blockConcurrencyWhile usage
- [ ] Test verifies single initialization

## Implementation
Move schema initialization to constructor with blockConcurrencyWhile.

## Architecture
```typescript
export class DO extends Agent {
  private initialized = false;

  constructor(state: DurableObjectState, env: Env) {
    super(state, env);

    state.blockConcurrencyWhile(async () => {
      if (!this.initialized) {
        await this.initializeSchema();
        this.initialized = true;
      }
    });
  }

  private async initializeSchema(): Promise<void> {
    await SchemaMigrations.initialize(this.state.storage.sql);
  }
}
```

## Requirements
- Use blockConcurrencyWhile in constructor
- Single initialization with flag
- Handle initialization errors

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] blockConcurrencyWhile used
- [ ] Single initialization guaranteed
- [ ] Error handling in place
- [ ] All RED tests pass

