The GitStore class in packages/do/src/gitx.ts extensively uses `(this as any).ctx` to access the DO context, indicating missing or incomplete type definitions.

Current unsafe patterns (15+ occurrences):
```typescript
// packages/do/src/gitx.ts
constructor(ctx: unknown, env: Env) {
  super(ctx as any, env)  // line 105
}

private initGitSchema(): void {
  const ctx = (this as any).ctx  // line 146
  ctx.storage.sql.exec(...)
}
```

Problem: The DO class in do.ts has a protected `ctx` property but it's typed as the Cloudflare `DurableObjectState` which might not expose the `storage.sql` interface properly.

Recommended solution:

1. Define proper context interface:
```typescript
interface DOContext extends DurableObjectState {
  storage: SqlStorage & {
    sql: SqlExecInterface
  }
}
```

2. Update DO base class to expose properly typed context:
```typescript
export class DO {
  protected ctx: DOContext
  // ...
}
```

3. Update GitStore to use proper inheritance:
```typescript
export class GitStore extends DO {
  constructor(ctx: DOContext, env: Env) {
    super(ctx, env)
  }

  private initGitSchema(): void {
    this.ctx.storage.sql.exec(...)  // Now properly typed
  }
}
```

This will eliminate all 15+ `(this as any).ctx` patterns in gitx.ts.

