design:
## Implementation

Create queue with push/pop, consumer registration, and backpressure.

### Core Implementation

```typescript
// packages/glyphs/src/queue.ts

interface QueueOptions {
  maxSize?: number
  timeout?: number
  concurrency?: number
}

interface Queue<T> {
  // Tagged template for push
  (strings: TemplateStringsArray, ...values: unknown[]): Promise<void>

  // Basic operations
  push(item: T): Promise<void>
  pop(): Promise<T | undefined>
  peek(): T | undefined

  // Batch operations
  pushMany(items: T[]): Promise<void>
  popMany(count: number): Promise<T[]>

  // Consumer pattern
  process(handler: (item: T) => Promise<void>, options?: ProcessOptions): () => void

  // State
  length: number
  isEmpty: boolean
  isFull: boolean
}

interface ProcessOptions {
  concurrency?: number
  retries?: number
  retryDelay?: number
}
```

### Factory Function

```typescript
// Create typed queue
const taskQueue = 卌<Task>()
const messageQueue = 卌<Message>({ maxSize: 1000 })
```

### Tagged Template Usage

```typescript
// Push to default queue
await 卌`task ${taskData}`

// Push with named queue
await 卌`email:send ${emailData}`
```

### Consumer Pattern

```typescript
// Register processor
const stop = 卌.process(async (task) => {
  await processTask(task)
})

// With options
const stop = taskQueue.process(async (task) => {
  await processTask(task)
}, {
  concurrency: 5,
  retries: 3,
  retryDelay: 1000
})

// Stop processing
stop()
```

### Backpressure

```typescript
const q = 卌<Task>({ maxSize: 100 })

// push() will wait if queue is full
await q.push(task) // blocks until space available

// Or check manually
if (!q.isFull) {
  await q.push(task)
}
```

### Implementation Details

1. Use array or linked list for queue storage
2. EventEmitter for consumer notification
3. Semaphore for concurrency control
4. Exponential backoff for retries
5. Graceful shutdown for process() consumers
6. Memory-bounded with maxSize option

### ASCII Alias

```typescript
export { createQueue as 卌, createQueue as q }
```

